      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rotating the RTC role each train prevents single-person bottlenecks and spreads cross-team context across the engineering org. Keep a rotation calendar visible in the release planning document."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Dependency Registration at Kick-Off"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each team that participates in a train must register their dependencies at kick-off using a shared YAML file committed to the repo. This makes implicit dependencies explicit and queryable:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# trains/train-42/dependencies.yml\ntrain: 42\nkick_off: 2025-07-29\ndeploy_target: 2025-08-12\ncoordinator: alice\n\nteams:\n  platform:\n    owner: \"@bob\"\n    delivers:\n      - id: api-gateway-v3.2\n        description: \"Rate limiting headers for downstream consumers\"\n        needed_by: [\"product\", \"ml\"]\n        ready_by: 2025-08-05   # must be merged before cut-line\n    depends_on: []\n\n  ml:\n    owner: \"@carol\"\n    delivers:\n      - id: model-router-v2.1\n        description: \"Weighted routing for claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\"\n        needed_by: [\"product\"]\n        ready_by: 2025-08-07\n    depends_on:\n      - team: platform\n        item: api-gateway-v3.2\n        blocking: true          # train cannot ship without this\n\n  infra:\n    owner: \"@dave\"\n    delivers:\n      - id: k8s-upgrade\n        description: \"Node pool upgrade to 1.29\"\n        needed_by: [\"platform\", \"ml\", \"product\"]\n        ready_by: 2025-08-04\n    depends_on: []\n\n  product:\n    owner: \"@eve\"\n    delivers:\n      - id: ui-dashboard-v1.3\n        description: \"Token usage dashboard using new rate limit headers\"\n        needed_by: []\n        ready_by: 2025-08-09\n    depends_on:\n      - team: platform\n        item: api-gateway-v3.2\n        blocking: true\n      - team: ml\n        item: model-router-v2.1\n        blocking: false         # nice-to-have but product can ship without it\n\n  support:\n    owner: \"@frank\"\n    delivers:\n      - id: runbook-updates\n        description: \"Updated runbooks for model router weighted routing\"\n        needed_by: []\n        ready_by: 2025-08-11   # day before deploy\n    depends_on:\n      - team: ml\n        item: model-router-v2.1\n        blocking: true\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A script validates this file at CI time to catch circular dependencies and missing `ready_by` dates:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"validate_deps.py \u2014 CI check for train dependency file.\"\"\"\nimport sys, yaml\nfrom datetime import date\n\ndef load(path: str) -> dict:\n    with open(path) as f:\n        return yaml.safe_load(f)\n\ndef validate(cfg: dict) -> list[str]:\n    errors = []\n    today = date.today()\n    deploy = date.fromisoformat(cfg[\"deploy_target\"])\n    teams = cfg[\"teams\"]\n    known_ids = {\n        item[\"id\"]\n        for team in teams.values()\n        for item in team.get(\"delivers\", [])\n    }\n    for team_name, team in teams.items():\n        for item in team.get(\"delivers\", []):\n            ready = date.fromisoformat(item[\"ready_by\"])\n            if ready > deploy:\n                errors.append(\n                    f\"{team_name}/{item['id']}: ready_by {item['ready_by']} is after deploy {deploy}\"\n                )\n        for dep in team.get(\"depends_on\", []):\n            if dep[\"item\"] not in known_ids:\n                errors.append(\n                    f\"{team_name} depends on unknown item '{dep['item']}'\"\n                )\n    return errors\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    cfg = load(sys.argv[1])\n    errs = validate(cfg)\n    if errs:\n        print(\"Dependency validation FAILED:\")\n        for e in errs:\n            print(f\"  - {e}\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    print(f\"Train {cfg['train']} dependency file is valid ({len(cfg['teams'])} teams).\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Daily Status Updates During Freeze Week"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "During the final week before deploy, the RTC posts a daily status update to the shared release channel. This is a structured format, not a free-form message \u2014 structure lets readers scan in 30 seconds:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "markdown"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "**Train 42 \u2014 Day 10 status (2025-08-11)**\n\n**Deploy target:** 2025-08-12 10:00 UTC\n**Coordinator:** @alice\n\n**Dependency status:**\n\n| Deliverable | Team | Ready | Blocking |\n|------------|------|-------|---------|\n| api-gateway-v3.2 | Platform | \u2705 Merged | Yes |\n| model-router-v2.1 | ML | \u2705 Merged | Yes |\n| k8s-upgrade | Infra | \u2705 Complete | Yes |\n| ui-dashboard-v1.3 | Product | \ud83d\udfe1 In review | No |\n| runbook-updates | Support | \ud83d\udfe1 Draft PR | Yes |\n\n**Blockers:**\n- runbook-updates PR (#1249) needs @ml-team review \u2014 @frank pinged, ETA 17:00 UTC\n\n**Go / No-go:** Conditional \u2014 runbook PR must merge before 08:00 UTC tomorrow\n\n**Actions:**\n- @frank: merge runbook PR tonight\n- @alice: confirm merge at 07:00 UTC, post go/no-go decision\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Automate the table generation from the dependency YAML to avoid manual errors \u2014 the RTC only fills in the status column:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"gen_status.py \u2014 generate daily status update skeleton from deps YAML.\"\"\"\nimport sys, yaml\n\ndef status_table(cfg: dict) -> str:\n    rows = []\n    for team_name, team in cfg[\"teams\"].items():\n        for item in team.get(\"delivers\", []):\n            blocking = \"Yes\" if any(\n                d[\"item\"] == item[\"id\"] and d[\"blocking\"]\n                for t in cfg[\"teams\"].values()\n                for d in t.get(\"depends_on\", [])\n            ) else \"No\"\n            rows.append(\n                f\"| {item['description'][:30]} | {team_name.title()} | \u2b1c TODO | {blocking} |\"\n            )\n    header = \"| Deliverable | Team | Ready | Blocking |\\n|------------|------|-------|---------|\"\n    return header + \"\\n\" + \"\\n\".join(rows)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    with open(sys.argv[1]) as f:\n        cfg = yaml.safe_load(f)\n    print(f\"**Train {cfg['train']} \u2014 Day X status**\\n\")\n    print(status_table(cfg))\n"
          }
        ]
      },
